WEBVTT

00:05.657 --> 00:07.659
♪

00:25.895 --> 00:28.289
DESSIE:
Election Day?

00:28.463 --> 00:30.508
JOSTO:
I think it's romantic.

00:30.682 --> 00:32.467
An Election Day wedding?

00:38.473 --> 00:40.866
It'll be a nice distraction
for Daddio,

00:41.041 --> 00:43.739
what with him having to wait
for the dead to vote.

00:45.784 --> 00:48.048
Isn't that right, Mayor Gillis?

00:53.183 --> 00:55.838
Oh, sugar bear,
you think of everything.

00:56.012 --> 00:58.928
I was thinking
maybe a June wedding.

00:59.102 --> 01:00.190
After.

01:00.364 --> 01:02.714
Why wait?

01:04.151 --> 01:06.109
Maybe we lose the election.

01:07.980 --> 01:11.462
And I got to rethink, are you
the right man for my Dessie?

01:11.636 --> 01:12.768
[laughs]:
Oh, Daddy.

01:12.942 --> 01:14.726
You're a four-alarm fire
sometimes.

01:14.900 --> 01:17.294
We're hopelessly in love.
Can't you see?

01:17.468 --> 01:18.904
[laughter]

01:22.778 --> 01:24.649
[chuckles]

01:24.823 --> 01:26.782
As hopeless as two turtle doves.

01:26.956 --> 01:28.610
And now that I'm all that stands

01:28.784 --> 01:31.482
between you and a lifetime
playing dogcatcher, I say,

01:31.656 --> 01:34.137
let's go ahead and get
this American dream started.

01:34.311 --> 01:35.791
[snaps fingers]

01:37.445 --> 01:38.446
Grazie.

01:38.620 --> 01:40.187
[laughs]

01:42.667 --> 01:44.278
[muffled grunting]

01:52.242 --> 01:54.201
[grunting continues]

01:58.857 --> 02:00.816
[soft music playing]

02:11.957 --> 02:13.655
[exhales]

02:13.829 --> 02:15.787
You like being a nurse?

02:17.615 --> 02:19.008
Mm-hmm.

02:19.182 --> 02:23.273
Well, I don't just like it.

02:23.447 --> 02:25.536
It's... it's my calling.

02:25.710 --> 02:27.669
Slick.

02:29.323 --> 02:32.064
Oh, by the by,
I'm getting married in March.

02:32.239 --> 02:33.327
What?

02:33.501 --> 02:35.329
It's just business.

02:35.503 --> 02:37.026
Shouldn't affect this.

02:38.506 --> 02:40.551
This?

02:40.725 --> 02:42.336
Didn't you say
you were in the hospital tons

02:42.510 --> 02:44.425
when you were a kid?

02:45.556 --> 02:47.776
Yeah.
Yes. I mean, yeah.

02:47.950 --> 02:50.257
My dear mama, she was...

02:50.431 --> 02:53.477
I was always quite sickly,
and she was...

02:53.651 --> 02:55.000
such a saint.

02:55.175 --> 02:57.220
God bless her,
she'd keep my spirits up.

02:57.394 --> 02:59.048
She'd put on little plays
with my dollies,

02:59.222 --> 03:00.832
have me rolling in the aisle.

03:01.006 --> 03:04.575
And she was very close
with the doctors.

03:04.749 --> 03:07.709
That's why I got
such excellent care.

03:07.883 --> 03:09.319
Slick.

03:09.493 --> 03:11.060
What was wrong with you?

03:11.234 --> 03:13.062
Oh, it was a...

03:13.236 --> 03:15.630
it was a kind of m-malaise.

03:17.066 --> 03:18.415
"Failure to thrive"

03:18.589 --> 03:20.939
is what I heard the doctors say
more than once.

03:21.113 --> 03:23.594
[sniffs]
I could barely keep food down.

03:23.768 --> 03:24.987
Sounds rough.

03:25.161 --> 03:26.945
Course, I had it worse.

03:27.119 --> 03:29.078
Are you really getting married?

03:29.252 --> 03:31.385
Oh, sure.
It's been on the books forever.

03:31.559 --> 03:32.995
-Mm-hmm.
-My pop arranged it.

03:33.169 --> 03:34.605
Do you love her?

03:34.779 --> 03:36.738
[Josto laughs]

03:38.609 --> 03:41.656
Wait, seriously?

03:41.830 --> 03:44.615
She...

03:44.789 --> 03:46.704
sh-sh...

03:46.878 --> 03:48.097
she knits.

03:48.271 --> 03:49.838
I knit.

03:50.012 --> 03:51.143
What kind of saint?

03:51.318 --> 03:54.451
-Huh?
-You said your mom was a saint.

03:54.625 --> 03:56.323
What kind, I'm asking.

03:56.497 --> 03:59.151
You know how, like, Jude was
the patron saint of lost causes,

03:59.326 --> 04:01.806
uh, Anastasia of Sirmium
was the patron saint

04:01.980 --> 04:05.636
of weavers, healers, martyrs
and, for some reason, exorcists.

04:05.810 --> 04:09.597
[sighs] She was just
the patron saint of me.

04:11.294 --> 04:14.776
She cared for your sweet
Oraetta patiently,

04:14.950 --> 04:17.431
without tiring,

04:17.605 --> 04:20.085
always making me
her special juice.

04:21.826 --> 04:23.785
Speaking of special juice...

04:32.968 --> 04:34.578
[door opens]

04:36.319 --> 04:37.929
[liquid splashing]

04:46.198 --> 04:47.852
WOMAN:
St. Thecla's Hospital,
may I help you?

04:48.026 --> 04:50.290
Ah, hello. This is, uh...

04:50.464 --> 04:52.553
M-Mabel Harvard.

04:52.727 --> 04:56.208
I-I wanted to call
to check in on my dear brother.

04:56.383 --> 04:59.690
Fell into a coma
three days past, poor boy.

04:59.864 --> 05:02.824
"On the way out" is what I...

05:02.998 --> 05:05.522
Sorry?

05:05.696 --> 05:08.656
When you say
h-he made a full recovery,

05:08.830 --> 05:09.874
what-what do you...

05:10.048 --> 05:11.920
[woman speaking indistinctly]

05:12.964 --> 05:14.792
Oh, that's...

05:14.966 --> 05:16.359
a joyous day that...

05:16.533 --> 05:18.840
And is, uh... is he, uh...

05:19.014 --> 05:21.451
Wh-What-what r...
what room is he in?

05:21.625 --> 05:23.584
I-I-I should visit.

05:23.758 --> 05:24.846
WOMAN:
I'm sorry, who did you say
you were again?

05:25.020 --> 05:27.022
His sister, like I said.

05:27.196 --> 05:29.677
[toilet flushes]

05:29.851 --> 05:31.243
Uh, well, n-never you mind.

05:31.418 --> 05:32.810
-Thank you for your time.
-[hangs up]

05:42.211 --> 05:43.517
What are you doing?

05:44.561 --> 05:46.737
I want to tell you a secret.

05:46.911 --> 05:48.870
That's... No, you don't
have to do that.

05:49.044 --> 05:50.872
Remember how I said my dad
gave me to another family

05:51.046 --> 05:52.395
when I was a kid?

05:52.569 --> 05:54.397
-No. You never...
-It was a power share.

05:54.571 --> 05:56.791
But here's the thing:

05:56.965 --> 06:00.185
The devil is an Irishman.

06:00.360 --> 06:02.710
I know, because I lived with him
for three years.

06:05.103 --> 06:07.367
And he did things to me.

06:07.541 --> 06:09.499
♪

06:12.284 --> 06:14.635
-Things you should
never do to a child.
-[shushes]

06:14.809 --> 06:17.246
[whispers]:
I don't want to hear about this.

06:20.205 --> 06:23.121
I know, I know.
It's tough stuff.

06:23.295 --> 06:26.124
But I like you, Minnesota.
You get me.

06:26.298 --> 06:28.431
-[sighs]
-And you shared
all that business

06:28.605 --> 06:30.477
about your failing to thrive.

06:31.956 --> 06:34.263
I'm saying I love you.
I think.

06:39.094 --> 06:40.095
Get out!

06:40.269 --> 06:41.966
[chuckles]

06:42.140 --> 06:43.751
Come on, beautiful.
Don't do this to yourself.

06:43.925 --> 06:45.535
No, I'm serious. You...

06:45.709 --> 06:50.801
You get the... you get the...
fuck out of my house!

06:50.975 --> 06:53.456
You make me sick!
Do you hear me?

06:53.630 --> 06:54.979
That's love!

06:55.153 --> 06:57.329
What it feels like.
Believe me, I know.

06:57.504 --> 06:59.767
I almost puked in your commode
just thinking about saying this.

07:02.770 --> 07:04.336
Slow your roll, toots.

07:04.511 --> 07:06.164
Romeo's beginning to feel
a little rejected here.

07:06.338 --> 07:08.819
[scoffs] Well, I hope
you have fun at your wedding.

07:08.993 --> 07:11.431
I'm afraid Oraetta Mayflower's
busy that day.

07:11.605 --> 07:13.171
I see, that's what this is.

07:13.345 --> 07:15.870
I swear, you women
and your jealousies.

07:17.524 --> 07:19.874
Don't be here when I get back!

07:23.660 --> 07:25.140
Dames.

07:25.314 --> 07:26.576
♪

07:49.991 --> 07:51.906
[indistinct chatter]

07:53.690 --> 07:55.605
What's this, now?

08:03.744 --> 08:05.746
[mutters]

08:05.920 --> 08:07.269
Aspet...
Aspettare.

08:07.443 --> 08:09.532
Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait.

08:09.706 --> 08:11.578
[grunts]

08:15.103 --> 08:17.627
[chuckles]

08:19.107 --> 08:21.022
[grunts]

08:21.196 --> 08:23.198
[gasping weakly]

08:34.775 --> 08:37.212
[Gaetano grunts]

08:46.656 --> 08:48.615
[Gaetano speaking Italian]

08:52.923 --> 08:55.056
[men laughing]

09:25.129 --> 09:26.653
[exhales]

09:28.176 --> 09:31.875
Who murdered a child
to have me killed.

09:32.049 --> 09:33.311
What?

09:33.485 --> 09:36.097
[chuckles]

09:38.621 --> 09:40.580
You murdered a child...

09:43.626 --> 09:45.585
...to have me killed.

09:49.501 --> 09:52.809
I'm so proud of you.
[laughing]

09:52.983 --> 09:55.377
My brother.

09:57.379 --> 09:59.816
Oh, he...

09:59.990 --> 10:02.471
he's clever, our enemy.

10:02.645 --> 10:03.864
The mulignan.

10:04.038 --> 10:06.431
Yeah.
When he let me go, I think,

10:06.606 --> 10:09.913
why does he do this?
Hmm?

10:10.087 --> 10:13.395
But then, I... I sit here.

10:15.179 --> 10:17.355
Waiting to kill you.

10:17.529 --> 10:20.489
And I realized

10:20.663 --> 10:23.492
he wants me to do this.

10:26.190 --> 10:30.107
To murder my brother
and take over this family.

10:33.154 --> 10:35.504
Because I'm the lion, but...

10:37.158 --> 10:39.508
...you're the snake.
[chuckles]

10:41.162 --> 10:43.164
I'm the what?

10:43.338 --> 10:45.383
What is happening right now?

10:45.557 --> 10:47.864
I think I'm-I'm still dreaming.

10:48.038 --> 10:49.431
[chuckles]
No.

10:49.605 --> 10:51.389
Hey, hey, no.

10:51.563 --> 10:53.609
Now, um...

11:04.794 --> 11:06.013
Yeah.

11:06.187 --> 11:07.492
I...

11:08.929 --> 11:11.975
[sighs]
I apologize, brother,

11:12.149 --> 11:15.936
because I think you're weak.

11:16.110 --> 11:19.113
But now I know what's true.

11:24.248 --> 11:26.120
[chuckles]

11:58.761 --> 12:01.416
I accept...

12:01.590 --> 12:04.332
this oath of poison,

12:04.506 --> 12:07.422
knowing that, from now on,

12:07.596 --> 12:09.685
no men will judge you...

12:11.426 --> 12:13.428
...but that you will
judge yourself.

12:15.299 --> 12:18.172
And if you ever betray me

12:18.346 --> 12:21.001
or this family...

12:35.145 --> 12:36.756
I swear.

12:46.809 --> 12:48.158
Come here.

12:48.332 --> 12:49.290
[Gaetano laughs]

12:49.464 --> 12:50.726
[grunts]

12:50.900 --> 12:53.294
[all cheering, clamoring]

12:57.646 --> 12:59.126
GAETANO:
Come on, come on.

12:59.300 --> 13:01.128
[applause]

13:11.486 --> 13:13.618
Tell me.

13:13.793 --> 13:15.969
It didn't work.

13:16.143 --> 13:18.623
They're a team now,
the brothers.

13:26.370 --> 13:28.329
So, what do we do?

13:33.160 --> 13:35.379
Fargo.

13:35.553 --> 13:37.512
[doorbell rings]

13:48.566 --> 13:49.567
We're closed.

13:49.741 --> 13:51.613
I'm here to see my son.

13:55.530 --> 13:56.836
You know who I am.

13:59.882 --> 14:01.449
Of course.

14:01.623 --> 14:03.364
Please, come in.

14:13.243 --> 14:15.593
I've been here before.

14:15.767 --> 14:18.901
Maybe... five years past.

14:19.075 --> 14:20.729
Friend of the family.

14:20.903 --> 14:23.253
Cancer.

14:23.427 --> 14:25.865
Y'all had a real nice service.

14:26.039 --> 14:28.302
We take our role here
very serious.

14:28.476 --> 14:30.739
-[chuckles]
-As the shepherd to the sheep.

14:32.436 --> 14:34.090
Got anything stronger?

14:34.264 --> 14:36.179
[soft chuckle]
Thurman keeps a bottle

14:36.353 --> 14:39.095
on the top shelf--
whiskey, I think.

14:39.269 --> 14:40.880
That'd do.

14:45.754 --> 14:47.408
I can't help you.

14:49.584 --> 14:51.325
What?

14:51.499 --> 14:54.110
You're going to pour me a drink,
and we're gonna get to talking.

14:54.284 --> 14:57.984
How we grew up
on the same street,

14:58.158 --> 15:00.595
know the same people,
and then...

15:00.769 --> 15:03.337
you're gonna ask me for help.

15:03.511 --> 15:06.035
And I want to go ahead
and let you know up front

15:06.209 --> 15:08.037
that's not going to happen.

15:10.300 --> 15:11.954
This is our home.

15:12.128 --> 15:15.436
Been in my husband's family
since the century's turn.

15:21.921 --> 15:24.401
People come to my husband,

15:24.575 --> 15:26.621
looking for money,

15:26.795 --> 15:29.319
at the end of their rope, and...

15:29.493 --> 15:32.105
and they all
think the same thing.

15:32.279 --> 15:34.803
"I've got nothing left to lose."

15:34.977 --> 15:36.196
But...

15:37.632 --> 15:40.635
...there's always lower
you can go.

15:48.512 --> 15:50.297
My youngest son was killed.

16:01.351 --> 16:04.746
W-We can't know his plans.

16:04.920 --> 16:07.662
All we can do is have faith.

16:09.316 --> 16:10.230
[quiet laugh]

16:10.404 --> 16:12.058
Amen.

16:14.886 --> 16:16.932
Does your eldest know?

16:29.205 --> 16:31.425
You have daughters also,
I think.

16:35.646 --> 16:37.126
Two.

16:38.562 --> 16:40.390
Mrs. Cannon,
we have made mistakes,

16:40.564 --> 16:42.218
my Thurman and me.

16:42.392 --> 16:44.568
Lord knows we're not
the angels we try to be.

16:44.742 --> 16:46.135
And we're not looking
for charity.

16:46.309 --> 16:48.572
Just the opportunity
to make things right.

16:48.746 --> 16:49.921
I told you...

16:50.096 --> 16:52.272
My girl turned
17 years old this week,

16:52.446 --> 16:55.144
with dreams
that take my breath away.

16:56.928 --> 17:00.497
It can't be that she falls
because...

17:00.671 --> 17:04.284
I was too stubborn or weak
to ask for help.

17:04.458 --> 17:07.069
We will make it right--
whatever it takes--

17:07.243 --> 17:09.376
if we get a fair shake.

17:20.952 --> 17:24.391
I wonder if you would
hold the service.

17:35.054 --> 17:37.056
It would be my honor.

17:39.536 --> 17:41.495
["Le Petit Homme" by Edith Piaf
playing]

18:00.731 --> 18:03.082
♪

18:14.745 --> 18:16.530
What are you studying there?

18:16.704 --> 18:17.966
Uh...

18:18.140 --> 18:19.794
French.

18:19.968 --> 18:21.970
Ooh la la.

18:25.756 --> 18:28.194
Uh, excuse you.

18:28.368 --> 18:30.892
You got some pretty decent
tunes here.

18:31.066 --> 18:32.807
Those are my dad's.

18:32.981 --> 18:35.244
Most of it's a little
off the cob.

18:35.418 --> 18:37.203
This one ain't half bad.

18:37.377 --> 18:38.813
You like jazz?

18:38.987 --> 18:40.336
Enough.

18:40.510 --> 18:41.903
Who's your favorite horn player?

18:42.077 --> 18:43.644
Mm...

18:43.818 --> 18:45.298
Louis Armstrong.

18:45.472 --> 18:47.430
Everybody says Louis.

18:47.604 --> 18:49.258
What about Dizzy?

18:49.432 --> 18:51.086
Or there's this new cat,
Charlie Parker.

18:51.260 --> 18:52.522
Everybody calls him Bird.

18:52.696 --> 18:54.785
It's a new sound-- no structure.

18:54.959 --> 18:57.788
Just... go where
the music takes you.

18:57.962 --> 18:59.703
I like structure.

18:59.877 --> 19:01.705
Yeah, I would've guessed that.

19:01.879 --> 19:03.185
[quiet laugh]

19:03.359 --> 19:05.013
How come you know
so much about music?

19:05.187 --> 19:06.667
I'm a horn player.

19:06.841 --> 19:08.147
Trumpet.

19:08.321 --> 19:10.018
Then why you lugging boxes?

19:10.192 --> 19:11.324
Oh, that?

19:11.498 --> 19:13.500
That's just an experience.

19:13.674 --> 19:15.197
Everything in life's
an experience,

19:15.371 --> 19:17.678
from climbing a mountain
to scrubbing a toilet.

19:19.114 --> 19:20.855
You climbed a mountain?

19:21.029 --> 19:22.422
No, but I've scrubbed
a few toilets.

19:22.596 --> 19:24.032
[Dibrell clears throat]

19:32.214 --> 19:34.347
Your mama's here for you.

19:43.747 --> 19:45.706
Poor boy.

19:47.795 --> 19:50.711
You keep your distance from him.

19:50.885 --> 19:52.756
You hear me?

19:52.930 --> 19:55.411
-I didn't do anything.
-He's your captor.

19:55.585 --> 19:57.544
Not your friend.

19:59.633 --> 20:01.896
And you can't afford
to make mistakes.

20:02.070 --> 20:04.377
♪

20:10.905 --> 20:12.559
[sighs]

20:34.842 --> 20:36.147
[stammering]

20:36.322 --> 20:37.932
N-Nurse Tapley,
might I have a word?

20:38.106 --> 20:39.760
-I'm on rounds.
-O-Of course, it's just,

20:39.934 --> 20:42.415
I heard Dr. Harvard took a turn
for the worse, poor soul.

20:42.589 --> 20:44.330
And I can't seem to find
the room number

20:44.504 --> 20:46.680
-in-in-in-in the ledger.
-He's been transferred.

20:46.854 --> 20:50.249
-Transferred?
-To a hospital specializing
in the treatment of poisons.

20:51.772 --> 20:53.121
[stammers]
To the, uh....

20:53.295 --> 20:55.558
Attempted murder,
the authorities think.

20:56.951 --> 20:59.345
-No.
-I kid you not.

20:59.519 --> 21:02.130
I saw the test results myself--
positive for strychnine.

21:02.304 --> 21:04.045
So, given the attempt prior

21:04.219 --> 21:06.177
resulting in the shooting death
of Mrs. Will,

21:06.352 --> 21:08.571
the authorities thought it best
to transfer Dr. Harvard

21:08.745 --> 21:10.660
out of state until he can make
a full recovery

21:10.834 --> 21:13.272
and offer evidence
on his assailant.

21:15.491 --> 21:17.450
Geez.

21:25.675 --> 21:27.634
♪

21:49.003 --> 21:50.961
[muttering]

21:56.010 --> 21:59.143
Been here before you...

21:59.318 --> 22:01.320
[continues muttering]

22:04.540 --> 22:05.976
[object clatters]

22:07.761 --> 22:09.763
[clattering]

22:11.112 --> 22:12.679
[huffs]

22:14.202 --> 22:16.030
[coughing]

22:28.651 --> 22:30.610
♪

22:42.752 --> 22:44.841
ETHELRIDA:
Dear Dr. Harvard,

22:45.015 --> 22:48.149
I've worked alongside
Oraetta Mayflower

22:48.323 --> 22:50.107
for many years now

22:50.281 --> 22:53.284
and felt that I should bring
certain actions of hers

22:53.459 --> 22:55.243
to your attention.

22:55.417 --> 22:58.638
In the last year, many
of Nurse Mayflower's patients

22:58.812 --> 23:02.163
have died under
mysterious circumstances.

23:02.337 --> 23:04.426
After each death,

23:04.600 --> 23:06.776
Mrs. Mayflower
has made it a habit

23:06.950 --> 23:09.039
to attend their funerals.

23:09.213 --> 23:11.955
She has also been known
to steal personal items

23:12.129 --> 23:14.610
from her patients
after their death.

23:14.784 --> 23:16.699
Not to mention...

23:16.873 --> 23:19.136
I have it upon good authority

23:19.310 --> 23:20.921
that she has pilfered
an abundance

23:21.095 --> 23:23.489
of potent narcotics
from the hospitals

23:23.663 --> 23:26.796
at which she has
been stationed.

23:26.970 --> 23:30.104
Dead patients, misappropriated personal items,

23:30.278 --> 23:32.454
stolen medication.

23:32.628 --> 23:34.804
I suppose
you have to ask yourself

23:34.978 --> 23:37.111
is this the kind of nurse

23:37.285 --> 23:40.201
you trust around patients
in your fine establishment?

23:56.173 --> 23:58.306
I'm gonna change my clothes
and splash my face.

23:58.480 --> 24:01.135
I'll be right here.

24:01.309 --> 24:02.876
[sighs]

24:03.050 --> 24:05.052
[sniffs]

24:05.226 --> 24:07.228
[door opens]

24:08.838 --> 24:10.797
[door closes]

24:17.847 --> 24:19.153
[car door opens]

24:26.160 --> 24:28.031
Nope.

24:28.205 --> 24:30.904
You're in the wrong
neighborhood, slim.

24:31.078 --> 24:33.776
You need to turn your ass around
and hop on back to your ride.

24:33.950 --> 24:35.909
Don't worry.
I got no wares to sell.

24:37.606 --> 24:39.216
Oh.

24:39.390 --> 24:41.741
I got me one of those, too.

24:41.915 --> 24:44.700
Makes a pretty sound
when it fires.

24:44.874 --> 24:47.050
Kind of like...
Chinese New Year.

24:47.224 --> 24:49.052
But maybe instead
of the six-shooter,

24:49.226 --> 24:50.837
you'd rather see my badge.

24:51.011 --> 24:52.839
I keep it real shiny.

24:53.013 --> 24:54.580
U.S. Marshal.

24:54.754 --> 24:57.713
Backed by the power
of the mighty American eagle.

24:57.887 --> 25:01.412
And if that old raptor
could talk, he'd say, "Son,

25:01.587 --> 25:04.503
"stand aside now,
for there's no power on earth

25:04.677 --> 25:08.985
that can keep a U.S. lawman
from the execution of his duty."

25:15.862 --> 25:18.473
You want me to say
all that again?

25:38.580 --> 25:41.235
[footsteps approaching]

25:41.409 --> 25:42.845
Just gonna fix myself a drink.

25:43.019 --> 25:45.413
-Would you like a drink?
-Thank you, no.

25:45.587 --> 25:48.938
For the Lord is my Shepherd,
and as a wise man once said,

25:49.112 --> 25:51.898
"Alcohol is your friend--
with a knife."

25:53.595 --> 25:54.770
My family's someplace safe.

25:54.944 --> 25:57.120
Not even you can find 'em.

25:57.294 --> 26:00.036
I'm not looking for your family.

26:00.210 --> 26:02.125
Is it still Thursday?

26:02.299 --> 26:04.911
These days feel like
they run together.

26:06.042 --> 26:07.522
I know what you mean.

26:07.696 --> 26:10.307
I came to your fair city
to do a simple job

26:10.481 --> 26:13.441
what feels like ages ago,
and yet... [sighs]

26:13.615 --> 26:15.443
here's me, still--

26:15.617 --> 26:18.098
bamboozled at every turn.

26:20.056 --> 26:23.451
I told those ladies
no harm would come to them.

26:23.625 --> 26:25.671
That makes me accountable.

26:28.978 --> 26:30.806
Should I tell you
what I've learned

26:30.980 --> 26:33.156
about the criminal mindset?

26:33.330 --> 26:36.986
By definition, the criminal
rejects accountability,

26:37.160 --> 26:40.903
as their identity is based
on getting away with things.

26:41.077 --> 26:43.079
Similarly, the criminal--

26:43.253 --> 26:45.168
you--

26:45.342 --> 26:48.476
rejects morality and ethics,
for if there is a larger right,

26:48.650 --> 26:51.348
then the criminal himself
is always wrong.

26:51.522 --> 26:53.829
And you don't strike me
as the type of man

26:54.003 --> 26:55.614
thinks himself wrong.

26:57.137 --> 26:58.442
Rarely.

26:58.617 --> 27:02.011
So there goes morality
out the window.

27:02.185 --> 27:03.665
But into that vacuum,

27:03.839 --> 27:06.973
what should rush but a code.

27:07.147 --> 27:09.497
A system of rules,

27:09.671 --> 27:12.761
mostly having to do
with loyalty.

27:12.935 --> 27:15.198
And this way,
the criminal detaches himself

27:15.372 --> 27:17.940
from the civilian world.

27:20.813 --> 27:22.728
And yet, here I am.

27:22.902 --> 27:26.383
Family man.
Community leader.

27:26.557 --> 27:28.559
Deacon in the church.

27:28.734 --> 27:31.606
[laughs]: Oh, the criminal
is capable of being

27:31.780 --> 27:33.782
all of those things.

27:33.956 --> 27:36.045
But it's a ruse.

27:36.219 --> 27:39.048
For though you claim to share
the values of your...

27:39.222 --> 27:41.529
wife or preacher,

27:41.703 --> 27:44.532
the Lord knows it's a disguise.

27:44.706 --> 27:46.839
Ask me how I know for certain.

27:47.883 --> 27:49.580
How do you know for certain?

27:49.755 --> 27:51.582
Would a family man trade
his youngest son to his enemy

27:51.757 --> 27:54.194
in exchange for power
and monetary gain?

27:58.546 --> 28:00.200
You need to leave.

28:04.204 --> 28:06.597
And so we circle back,

28:06.772 --> 28:08.121
inevitably,

28:08.295 --> 28:09.688
to your original statement--

28:09.862 --> 28:11.777
to wit, I'm accountable
for those ladies,

28:11.951 --> 28:13.561
murderers both,
thieves and cheats.

28:13.735 --> 28:15.432
But now, since we both know

28:15.606 --> 28:18.348
the criminal is capable
of love and loyalty

28:18.522 --> 28:21.438
only when it suits
his own self-interest,

28:21.612 --> 28:24.572
I've come to make
the following point.

28:24.746 --> 28:26.705
It don't.

28:28.228 --> 28:30.665
Not no more.

28:33.494 --> 28:35.322
In summation, boy,

28:35.496 --> 28:37.933
if you could
sacrifice your youngest,

28:38.107 --> 28:40.370
like Isaac in the Holy Book,

28:40.544 --> 28:42.590
well, then giving up
two strangers

28:42.764 --> 28:45.724
to keep the might of the federal
government off your back...

28:47.464 --> 28:50.380
...well, now, that should be
as facile as breathing.

28:54.384 --> 28:56.212
[laughing]

28:59.476 --> 29:01.174
[Loy laughing]

29:02.653 --> 29:04.960
[smacks lips]
I like you.

29:05.134 --> 29:07.267
[chuckles]

29:07.441 --> 29:09.922
We Mormons
are very friendly people.

29:10.096 --> 29:11.575
No.

29:11.750 --> 29:13.664
Pretty unfriendly, really,

29:13.839 --> 29:17.277
but it's the way
you're unfriendly.

29:17.451 --> 29:19.758
Like you're doing me a favor.

29:23.762 --> 29:27.069
They're on the 10:00 train
to Philadelphia.

29:27.243 --> 29:29.202
You didn't hear it from me.

29:32.466 --> 29:34.642
DEAFY:
Hmm. See?

29:36.165 --> 29:39.168
I knew we could figure
this thing out

29:39.342 --> 29:42.781
if we just...
put our minds to it.

29:46.697 --> 29:50.223
You want my advice?

29:50.397 --> 29:53.052
When you cross the state line,
don't come back.

29:53.226 --> 29:55.968
It ain't safe for you
in Missouri no more.

29:57.796 --> 29:59.798
You boys have a nice day.

30:06.413 --> 30:08.023
On my signal,

30:08.197 --> 30:10.069
Alpha Team will enter
through the main doors.

30:10.243 --> 30:11.853
Beta Team will penetrate

30:12.027 --> 30:13.855
-through the rear.
-[men chuckling]

30:14.029 --> 30:16.336
Someone want
to let me in on the joke?

30:18.555 --> 30:22.342
Fine. It's the 10:00
to Philadelphia, track three.

30:23.386 --> 30:25.171
Remember, these subjects

30:25.345 --> 30:27.521
are to be considered
armed and extremely dangerous.

30:27.695 --> 30:29.828
Any questions?

30:31.568 --> 30:34.310
Then let us bow our heads
for Psalm 91:3.

30:36.095 --> 30:39.185
"Surely he will save you
from the fowler's snare and...

30:39.359 --> 30:41.752
"from the deadly pestilence.

30:41.927 --> 30:44.494
He will cover you
with his feathers."

30:45.713 --> 30:46.975
Amen.

30:47.149 --> 30:48.890
OTHERS:
Amen.

30:49.064 --> 30:50.718
Dismissed.

30:52.328 --> 30:54.287
[indistinct chatter]

31:05.298 --> 31:07.953
If it's copacetic with you,
I-I want in.

31:10.085 --> 31:12.958
Look, I've been thinking
about what you said.

31:14.263 --> 31:16.091
I just want to be a cop again.

31:16.265 --> 31:18.180
No bullshit.
All-in.

31:19.747 --> 31:20.879
Sure, partner.

31:21.053 --> 31:22.881
Just tell me one thing.

31:23.055 --> 31:24.447
Who was on the phone?

31:24.621 --> 31:26.362
And before you lie,

31:26.536 --> 31:28.799
just know I ain't been fooled
by man or beast

31:28.974 --> 31:31.890
since Hitler was still giving
speeches in beer halls.

31:36.242 --> 31:37.721
It was Loy Cannon.

31:40.463 --> 31:42.074
Go on.

31:43.814 --> 31:46.078
He wants me to make sure
you get those girls.

31:46.252 --> 31:48.602
Doesn't want them
coming back on him.

31:48.776 --> 31:49.995
Get how?

31:50.169 --> 31:51.779
Just...

31:51.953 --> 31:53.607
to make sure they're caught.

31:53.781 --> 31:55.261
Or killed.

31:59.743 --> 32:01.093
Okay, then.

32:02.616 --> 32:04.444
Now, what was it you were saying

32:04.618 --> 32:07.099
about being a cop again?

32:07.273 --> 32:09.231
I...

32:11.842 --> 32:15.107
This is... this isn't a choice.

32:15.281 --> 32:17.109
I got a condition.

32:17.283 --> 32:19.111
When I was a kid,

32:19.285 --> 32:21.678
the teachers said
"oversensitive."

32:21.852 --> 32:24.377
The army shrink told me
I-I worried too much, which...

32:24.551 --> 32:26.640
How can you worry too much
when you're at war?

32:28.033 --> 32:29.904
Those things you called me--

32:30.078 --> 32:32.298
twitchy, touched--

32:32.472 --> 32:34.387
I been hearing that
my whole life.

32:36.084 --> 32:37.999
All I know is I-I feel better
when I'm in charge,

32:38.173 --> 32:39.740
when I got the power.

32:39.914 --> 32:41.742
That's why I joined the force.

32:41.916 --> 32:43.657
You know,
because cops have power.

32:43.831 --> 32:45.528
So, now I'm on the street.
I'm the boss.

32:45.702 --> 32:48.705
Except, turns out,
being a cop's real risky.

32:48.879 --> 32:50.751
Risky makes me nervous.

32:50.925 --> 32:54.189
So I m...
I make a deal with the street.

32:54.363 --> 32:57.149
I take a few bucks,
I-I look the other way.

32:58.585 --> 33:00.935
Less risk,
but also less power.

33:02.371 --> 33:04.765
So here comes
that feeling again.

33:04.939 --> 33:06.375
Like I'm...

33:06.549 --> 33:09.509
I'm drowning on-on dry land.

33:17.343 --> 33:19.301
You know what worries me?

33:20.868 --> 33:23.218
Dying with one boot on,

33:23.392 --> 33:24.828
caught short.

33:26.569 --> 33:28.528
That's a petty death.

33:31.574 --> 33:33.837
So, let me throw you a rope.

33:34.012 --> 33:35.404
You want to die like a man,

33:35.578 --> 33:37.015
you got to live like a man.

33:41.193 --> 33:42.672
I'm ready.

33:45.371 --> 33:47.329
Giddyup.

33:48.983 --> 33:50.811
[indistinct conversations]

33:50.985 --> 33:52.900
[indistinct announcements
over P.A.]

34:13.790 --> 34:15.488
I want to get some sweets.

34:15.662 --> 34:18.056
That sweet tooth's gonna
kill you one of these days.

34:18.230 --> 34:20.449
I'll wrestle you a lollipop.

34:20.623 --> 34:22.582
Go on, then, shake a leg.

34:29.415 --> 34:30.938
What'll it be, sir?

34:31.112 --> 34:32.940
Give me five of them Clarks,

34:33.114 --> 34:35.899
three Bit-O-Honeys
and a couple Abba-Zabbas.

34:41.905 --> 34:43.907
♪

34:58.226 --> 35:00.620
Hallowed be thy name.

35:07.540 --> 35:09.324
Five little, six little, four
little, five little, six...

35:09.498 --> 35:12.066
Cheer up, palomino.

35:14.112 --> 35:16.331
-[muttering]
-In times like these,
my mind goes back

35:16.505 --> 35:18.507
to the wisest words
I ever heard.

35:18.681 --> 35:20.509
And forgive me for the blueness

35:20.683 --> 35:24.122
of the final stanza,
but here it is.

35:25.514 --> 35:28.038
"Behold the amazing pelican,

35:28.213 --> 35:30.650
"whose beak can hold more
than his belly can.

35:30.824 --> 35:33.305
"He can hold in his beak
enough food for a week.

35:33.479 --> 35:36.830
I'll be damned
if I know how the hell he can."

35:40.964 --> 35:43.053
Geronimo.

35:43.228 --> 35:45.665
-[car door closes]
-Six little, seven...

35:53.716 --> 35:55.675
[car doors closing]

35:58.634 --> 36:00.984
[muttering]

36:06.860 --> 36:08.731
Stupid. Stupid.

36:08.905 --> 36:10.733
[indistinct announcements
over P.A.]

36:10.907 --> 36:12.866
[indistinct conversations]

36:19.394 --> 36:21.353
[laughs]

36:23.746 --> 36:26.140
[both chuckle]

36:29.709 --> 36:30.753
Mm.

36:30.927 --> 36:33.669
I'm liable to miss this place.

36:33.843 --> 36:35.236
I's just gettin' accustomed.

36:35.410 --> 36:37.499
[chuckles]
You and me both.

36:37.673 --> 36:39.936
Mm.
Hittin' them Eyeties

36:40.110 --> 36:41.460
was some of the most fun
I ever had.

36:41.634 --> 36:43.810
-[chuckles]
-Barrel of monkeys.

36:43.984 --> 36:45.551
[laughs]

36:51.426 --> 36:54.429
Our objective
is to bring 'em in alive.

36:54.603 --> 36:56.039
But if they engage,

36:56.214 --> 36:57.606
drop 'em where they stand.

36:57.780 --> 36:59.347
Let's go.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.892
ZELMARE:
Rattler's almost here.

37:29.812 --> 37:33.076
♪

37:48.918 --> 37:51.530
[baby crying in distance]

37:58.754 --> 37:59.842
[rapid footsteps]

38:00.016 --> 38:02.280
[door opens, closes]

38:10.505 --> 38:12.290
[wheels squeaking]

38:18.426 --> 38:20.385
[indistinct announcement
over P.A.]

38:49.805 --> 38:51.503
♪

38:57.552 --> 38:59.511
[gun cocks]

39:15.265 --> 39:17.311
♪

39:34.546 --> 39:36.112
[gun cocks]

39:36.286 --> 39:39.507
Come get it, dirty coppers!

39:39.681 --> 39:41.727
-[gunfire continuing]
-[people screaming]

40:04.140 --> 40:06.273
Just go. Go.

40:06.447 --> 40:08.275
Go. Just go.

40:08.449 --> 40:10.146
Go. Go. Go!

40:10.320 --> 40:12.497
Go! Go! Go!
[grunts]

40:12.671 --> 40:14.455
-[shouting, screaming]
-[gunfire in distance]

40:14.629 --> 40:16.588
[sirens wailing in distance]

40:25.248 --> 40:27.207
[panting]

40:32.647 --> 40:34.127
[grunts]

40:44.311 --> 40:45.791
[grunts, panting]

40:47.532 --> 40:49.447
One little, two little,
three little...

40:49.621 --> 40:51.231
four little,
five little...

40:52.493 --> 40:53.494
Six...

40:53.668 --> 40:55.670
Jesus.

40:55.844 --> 40:57.846
Ten...

40:58.020 --> 41:00.153
One little,
two little...

41:00.327 --> 41:02.068
Five, six...

41:04.026 --> 41:05.463
Ten little Indians.
Ten...

41:07.769 --> 41:09.162
Seven...

41:14.776 --> 41:16.604
Ten little...

41:16.778 --> 41:18.737
♪

41:23.132 --> 41:25.091
[gunfire in distance]

41:26.875 --> 41:28.834
[rapid gunfire in distance]

41:30.357 --> 41:32.315
DEAFY [in distance]:
Drop your weapons!

41:34.709 --> 41:36.537
Drop 'em now, ladies!

41:36.711 --> 41:38.670
[guns clatter]

41:39.888 --> 41:42.325
Over here, I got 'em.

41:42.500 --> 41:44.327
They ran out of bullets.

41:48.462 --> 41:50.377
Attaboy, Weff.

41:51.900 --> 41:54.033
Come on.
I need you.

41:56.514 --> 41:57.863
Cuff 'em.

42:07.655 --> 42:08.874
[grunts]

42:22.235 --> 42:24.237
[distorted wail]

42:35.814 --> 42:36.858
[screams]

42:41.297 --> 42:43.299
[grunts, panting]

42:43.473 --> 42:44.866
[grunting]

43:11.153 --> 43:13.112
♪

43:19.161 --> 43:20.728
Four little, five little...

43:22.643 --> 43:24.253
Four little, five little...

43:25.994 --> 43:27.953
♪

43:41.270 --> 43:43.229
[crow caws]

43:54.762 --> 43:56.721
[indistinct conversation]

44:11.039 --> 44:13.302
Josto!

44:22.485 --> 44:24.836
Drink.

44:28.666 --> 44:31.103
[chuckles]

44:43.942 --> 44:46.684
I sent him after Milligan
and the kid.

44:46.858 --> 44:48.598
Huh?

44:48.773 --> 44:52.211
Antoon was supposed
to shoot the kid,

44:52.385 --> 44:55.083
but... Milligan shot him first,

44:55.257 --> 44:56.606
took the kid,
and they flew the coop.

44:56.781 --> 44:59.697
So Calamita's
gonna run 'em down.

45:02.743 --> 45:05.746
So you tell our enemy
his son is dead?

45:05.920 --> 45:07.966
[laughs]

45:08.140 --> 45:11.491
Uh, how you know Irish
doesn't run straight to him?

45:15.800 --> 45:17.802
[laughing]

45:19.586 --> 45:20.761
Mwah.

45:20.935 --> 45:22.589
Josto...

45:22.763 --> 45:24.069
the python.

45:24.243 --> 45:26.898
[grunts, laughs]

45:27.072 --> 45:28.116
No, come here.

45:28.290 --> 45:29.901
Come here, come here.

45:30.075 --> 45:32.120
-Ah. Proud of you.
-[door opens]

45:32.294 --> 45:34.296
CHIANNA:
Boys! Come inside.

45:34.470 --> 45:35.994
-It's freezing out.
-In a minute, Ma.
-Ah.

45:36.168 --> 45:38.431
-No, come now,
before you catch a cold.
-Mm.

45:38.605 --> 45:40.433
We're not little boys anymore.

45:40.607 --> 45:42.000
We don't catch cold.

45:42.174 --> 45:43.349
Ah.

45:43.523 --> 45:45.177
Such disrespect, huh?

45:45.351 --> 45:48.963
And me, just a poor old woman
who loves her sons.

45:49.137 --> 45:51.270
Oh, Mom, you know,
we love you.

45:51.444 --> 45:53.794
We're talking about business.
[speaks Italian]

45:53.968 --> 45:55.491
-Money.
-Mwah. Come in.

45:55.665 --> 45:56.971
-Mwah.
-Come on.

45:57.145 --> 45:59.757
[laughs]

46:03.891 --> 46:05.850
[water flowing]

46:21.039 --> 46:23.041
[speaking indistinctly]

46:45.150 --> 46:47.108
[muttering in Italian]

46:48.370 --> 46:50.982
Let's go!

46:51.156 --> 46:52.374
[gunfire continuing]

46:52.548 --> 46:55.247
[Gaetano shouting in Italian]

46:56.509 --> 46:57.771
[growls]

46:57.945 --> 47:00.034
[shouts]

47:00.208 --> 47:02.515
[grunts]

47:03.559 --> 47:05.170
[grunts]

47:07.694 --> 47:08.651
Josto!

47:08.826 --> 47:09.652
Gaetano!

47:09.827 --> 47:11.480
-You okay?
-Yeah.

47:11.654 --> 47:12.830
Are you okay?

47:15.528 --> 47:16.921
[Maxia screams]

47:17.095 --> 47:18.357
[screams]

47:18.531 --> 47:20.359
[crying]

47:20.533 --> 47:22.535
♪

49:58.169 --> 49:59.561
MAN:
Now I get it.

49:59.735 --> 50:01.085
[rooster crows]
